The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 6: The Lok Sabha today passed the prevention of money laundering bill with certain amendments to remove lacunae in the legislation. The bill, passed by a voice vote, provides that a police officer can investigate a money laundering offence under the act only after he has been specifically authorised by the central government. Finance minister P. Chidambaram said certain amendments had to be incorporated in the bill to rectify the shortcomings of the earlier legislation.

 New Delhi, May 6: Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) has renewed its $11 billion insurance policy for 2005-06 at a $19.95 million premium, which is 17 per cent lower than last year.

 New Delhi, May 6: The Union petroleum ministry expects the Iran-Pakistan-India pipeline ?to become a reality? by 2010, petroleum secretary S. C. Tripathi said today.

 New Delhi, May 6: The government is yet to take a decision on foreign equity participation in the pension sector, said S. S. Palanimanickam, minister of state for finance.

 Dhaka, May 6: Senior Tata officials will visit Bangladesh on Sunday to discuss its $2.5-billion investment plans in the neighbouring country. The company has already submitted the pre-feasibility study on the proposed investment.




